cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about training generative models with deep neural networks as generators. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the use of flexible code distributions to improve generative models. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Sound). These sub-categories are likely because the paper discusses the benefits of more powerful generative models, better modeling of latent structure, and explicit control of generalization, which are all relevant to these areas of computer science.
